{
  "text": "Enlarged Lysosome in ADA-deficient Cells-TRPML1-mediated lysosomal Ca 2\u03e9 release is essential for lysosomal membrane trafficking, and defective TRPML1 results in enlarged lysosomes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . The above results suggest that by affecting TRPML1mediated Ca 2\u03e9 release lysosomal adenosine accumulation in ADA \u03ea/\u03ea fibroblasts may result in enlarged lysosomes. In agreement with this, ADA \u03ea/\u03ea fibroblasts displayed enlarged lysosomes as revealed by electron microscopy, and this was rescued by ML-SA1 treatment (Fig. 4, A and B) . Overall, these results confirm that lysosomal adenosine accumulation inhibits TRPML1 activity, subsequently resulting in defective membrane trafficking.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "5123540",
